Okay, so a quick explanation of the roles:
or maybe open H2P while playing
Shapeshifter - each night can choose someone to kill, once per game they can "shift" into the person they chose to kill.

So if that was you and your avatar was Spiderman, you could choose to kill Hulk and shift him. The next morning, it would look to the Village that Spiderman had been killed at night, and you would now be talking as Hulk
Protector - each night, you can choose to protect someone from dying. If the wolf tries to kill them, no one will die. You can't target the same person two nights in a row.

Stalker - each night, you can choose to target someone and you will learn if they targeted another player. So you check Spiderman and you will be told if Spiderman visited anyone. If they visited the same person who died that night, you might have found the Wolf. If they visited someone who didn't die, you've probably found someone else Good.
Villager - No powers, just votes during the day, has to try and work out what is going on.
Sleepwalker - You are told you are a normal Villager, but at night, you randomly visit someone. You will not know your the Sleepwalker unless someone is telling you that you visited someone.
And finally Tanner - you want to die during the day, so you're trying to trick the Village into thinking your a Wolf.
So that is all the roles that will be in this game :)
There are: 1 Shapeshifter, 1 Tanner, 1 Villager, 1 Protector, 1 Stalker and 1 Sleepwalker.
